The application should consist of (i) a curriculum vitae, (ii) a =20
description of the
candidate's pedagogical project, (iii) a description of the research =20
project that the
candidate intends to pursue in the coming years,  (iv) a text =20
presenting the (up to
five) most significant publications of the candidate and (v) a copy of =20=

these most
significant publications (up to five).

The candidates are invited to use the standard model of curriculum =20
vitae proposed at
ULB. This model can be downloaded via the following link:

http://www.ulb.ac.be/facs/sciences/admin/docs-admin/Cvtype.rtf


